Package com.prc.alp.liaison.retsina Description

Provides tailored Web page parsing capabilities for RETSINA InfoAgents. (RETSINA stands for Reusable Environment for Task Structured Intelligent Network Agents.) Each InfoAgent requires a unique external query function it can invoke to extract information on demand from specified Web pages, which may be pre-saved locally or dynamically downloaded over the Internet.

Note: although the source files for these query functions are stored and compiled in a Liaison directory (com\prc\alp\liaison\retsina), they are built without a package declaration, and the .class files must moved manually to the appropriate RETSINA directory (typically, %ALP_INSTALL_PATH%\ext\retsina\actions). This is necessary for proper execution by the RETSINA InfoAgents. Because these classes have no package, their Javadoc documentation is also generated and indexed separately.

More information about RETSINA and InfoAgents can be found at the RETSINA project home pages here or here.
